<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="KR3l0099-en-924207ee" type="transl"><teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>Translation of 搜神記 into (English)</title><editor role="translator">Valerie Kiel</editor></titleStmt><publicationStmt><p>published electronically as part of the TLS project at https://hxwd.org</p><availability status="1">This work is in the public domain</availability></publicationStmt><sourceDesc><p>Created by members of the TLS project</p><p>Translation of <bibl corresp="#KR3l0099"><title xml:lang="och">搜神記</title></bibl> into <lang xml:lang="en">English</lang>.</p></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><creation resp="#CH">Initially created: <date>2021-06-14T03:26:55.809+09:00</date> by CH</creation></profileDesc></teiHeader><text><body><div><head>Translated parts</head><p xml:id="KR3l0099-start"><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-h" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-14T03:27:30.036+09:00">Preface</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T02:58:12.295+09:00">and I may have gathered left-out material from those times</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T03:37:50.827+09:00">and what presumably was heard or seen not just by one person's ears and one person's</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T02:59:21.084+09:00">but how would I then go on to presume to imagine that nothing there was without base.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T02:57:55.697+09:00">I may have investigated early records in the surviving documents,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:10:02.708+09:00">Wei Suo lost his state</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:10:55.326+09:00">and (regarding this fact) there are two conflicting oral reports.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:22:58.836+09:00">On Lü Wang's service to the Zhou</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:23:20.679+09:00">Zizhang preserves two explanations.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:43:00.769+09:00">Comparable examples of this kind</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:43:22.679+09:00">are often found in the records.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:44:39.387+09:00">From this point of view</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:45:03.019+09:00">the difficulty of oral and written evidence</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T04:45:38.452+09:00">has a very long history.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T05:05:31.15+09:00">The fixed formulations of the documents and funerary announcements</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-07-05T05:24:02.307+09:00">base themselves on the formal square volumes of state histories</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.16" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:21:22.5+09:00">and the situation remains the same.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.17" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:06:15.761+09:00">How much more will this be the case when one looks up and transmits what comes from a thousand years ago</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.18" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:06:51.694+09:00">and when one records systematic accounts of different customs</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.19" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:07:24.189+09:00">and sticks together disjointed words on damaged and deficient documents,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.20" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:08:23.008+09:00">when one seeks information on actions from old times</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.21" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:23:33.455+09:00">and insists on having things not look ambiguous</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.22" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:09:47.713+09:00">and one's account not to be contradictory</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.23" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:10:33.751+09:00">before they can be regarded reliable,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.24" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-08-23T03:19:51.36+09:00">then this is where former historical accounts inherently present problems.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.25" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:26:11.381+09:00">But if the states have not for that reason discontinued the offices of commentators and archivists</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.26" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:15:54.042+09:00">and if the scholars do not discontinue their business of reciting and reading their sources</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.27" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:17:20.423+09:00">surely this is because what they miss out on is of little importance, by comparison,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.28" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:17:05.666+09:00">and what they preserve this way is much more important.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.29" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:17:54.492+09:00">What I have collected at this point</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.30" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:18:22.952+09:00">setting out to continue what has been transmitted</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.31" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:18:39.744+09:00">cannot be deemed my fault.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.32" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:27:54.374+09:00">If in my modern enquiries in our present world</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.33" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:28:11.194+09:00">there are mistakes and confusions</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.34" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:28:52.894+09:00">it is my quiet hope to share with earlier worthies and earlier scholars</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.35" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T17:30:14.761+09:00">the criticism and maligning I will be exposed to.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.36" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:22:03.205+09:00">As I write up and transmit these things</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.37" xml:lang="en" resp="#CH" modified="2021-06-21T05:22:55.929+09:00">it will serve to throw light on what is not completely wrong in the way of the spirits.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.38" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:02:41.4+09:00">All talk, and all schools of thought</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.39" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:03:08.026+09:00">are impossible for one person to survey completely,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.40" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:03:20.429+09:00">what ears and eyes perceive</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.41" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:03:48.862+09:00">it is impossible to transmit completely.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.42" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:12:29.176+09:00">I will only make a rough choice sufficient to lay out the basis of the eight outlines</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.43" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:13:19.01+09:00">and to bring out the subtle messages, that is all.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.44" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:14:22.698+09:00">If we are lucky, in the future there will be eager squires</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.45" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T03:14:36.508+09:00">who will record the basic substance of the matter</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.46" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:09:31.905+09:00">and will have something to entertain their spirits with,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.47" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:09:42.061+09:00">to please the eye</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-1a.48" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:09:54.435+09:00">without making serious mistakes.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_000-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:10:03.67+09:00"/><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-h" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:10:33.435+09:00">Chapter One</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:14:41.578+09:00">Shen Nong has used his red whip to whip into life all (crop) plants.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:16:36.009+09:00">He completely understood the nature of healthy vs. poisonous and (medically) cold vs. warm.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:16:40.061+09:00">Focusing most on the flavour of things,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:17:24.456+09:00">he went on to sow (by spreading) all (crop) grains.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-1a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:18:19.226+09:00">That is why everyone style him the Spirit Farmer.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:19:04.667+09:00">(As for) Chi Songzi</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:19:35.744+09:00">he was the Rain God of the times of Shen Nong.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:22:01.833+09:00">He lived on frozen medicinal powder,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:22:09.583+09:00">a technique he taught Shen Nong.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:22:27.724+09:00">He could go through fire without getting burnt.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:24:20.422+09:00">he often entered the stone dwellings of the Queen Mother of the West,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:24:03.628+09:00">When he reached the Kunlun Mountains,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:24:59.628+09:00">rising and descending with the wind and the rain.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:26:58.096+09:00">The youngest daughter of the sovereign Yan, in pursuing him,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:27:16.837+09:00">also obtained supernatural status</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:27:47.343+09:00">and together, they departed (from this world).</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:28:20+09:00">When it came to the times of Gao Xin</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:28:53.762+09:00">he again became the Rain God (on Earth),</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.14" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:29:24.201+09:00">and wandered among men.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-2a.15" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:31:39.225+09:00">The institution of the Rain God nowadays had its origin in this.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:32:33.259+09:00">1.3 Chijiang Ziyu </seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:32:51.221+09:00">was a man from the times of the Yellow Emperor.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:33:01.382+09:00">He avoided eating any of the five grains</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:33:47.956+09:00">and nibbled flowers of various plants.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:34:04.357+09:00">When it came to the time of Yao,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:34:15.783+09:00">he became a carpenter.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:34:39.34+09:00">He could rise and descend with the wind and rain.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:36:41.421+09:00">At times, he sold strings at the market gates</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-3a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:36:49.123+09:00">therefore he was also called Old String.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:46:49.075+09:00">1.4 Ning Fengzi</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.2" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:37:27.959+09:00">was a man from the times of the Yellow Emperor.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.3" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:39:10.795+09:00">It is said nowadays that when he acted as the Yellow Emperor's Director of Pottery,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.4" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:39:49.354+09:00">a strange person came by</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.5" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:40:58.342+09:00">and served as his Fire Holder;</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.6" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:41:12.165+09:00">that person could blow smoke of five colours.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.7" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:41:34.762+09:00">In the long run, he taught Fengzi how to do this.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.8" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:42:33.652+09:00">When Fengzi had piled up fire so it burnt of itself,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.9" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:43:06.029+09:00">he would rise and descended following the smoke.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.10" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:44:07.105+09:00">When one inspected the cold embers,</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.11" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-08-04T04:33:40.756+09:00">there still were his bones in them.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.12" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:45:19.153+09:00">The people at the time combined forces to bury him (Fengzi) in the Ningshan Mountains.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-4a.13" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:46:16.838+09:00">That in fact is why they call him NING Fengzi.</seg><seg corresp="#KR3l0099_tls_001-5a.1" xml:lang="en" resp="#Valerie.Kiel" modified="2021-07-05T04:46:34.659+09:00">1.5 </seg></p></div></body></text></TEI>